President Muhammadu Buhari and other prominent APC members graced the wedding ceremony of Gov. Abdullahi Ganduje’s daughter, Hajiya Fatima, and her husband, Idris Ajimobi, a son of Oyo Gov. Isiaka Ajimobi in Kano.

The Islamic nuptials took place around 12:30 pm at the Kano Central Mosque.

Emir of Kano, Alhaji Muhammadu Sanusi II conducted the wedding, and was supported by 
the Chief Imam of Kano, Prof. Sani Zaharaddeen.

President Buhari, who stood for the groom, gave out N50, 000 as a bride price to Ahmed Bola Tunubu representing the bride on the occasion.

Other APC personalities in attendance were  Senate President Bukola Saraki, 22 governors and 11 ministers as well as over 10 traditional rulers from across the country.

Others were Secretary to the Government of the Federation Boss Mustapha, Chief of Staff to the President, Abba Kyari and Senior Special Assistant to President on Media and Publicity, Malam Garba Shehu, and members of the National Assembly.

Also present were members of the business community, politicians as well as members of the diplomat corps.

The President had before his departure inspected the Kofar Ruwa underpass, which is under construction, along Katsina Road.

 
